[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"letter_supporters\",\n    \"audience\": \"supporters\",\n    \"text\": \"Dear friends, Parkinson's disease has changed my rhythm, but not my resolve. I used to think I had to suffer in silence. Today I share a small victory: walking to the mailbox without my cane. Thank you for being with me.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"letter_newly_diagnosed\",\n    \"audience\": \"newly_diagnosed\",\n    \"text\": \"To anyone recently diagnosed: you are not a victim. Early on, I felt afflicted and alone. With practice and patience, my hands learned a gentler dance. We learn, we adapt, and we keep going.\"\n  }\n]\n